title: For Sale/Trade:  FS/FT CMMG M4LE + NICE EXTRAS
postcontent:
Offering for sale/for trade a like-new CMMG M4LE rifle. I'd call it 99% condition, it's been to the range one time and had 140rds fired. Some light handling marks on the buttstock, and one small slightly shiny spot on the barrel, otherwise very beautiful.
This rifle is a no-nonsense 16" barreled M4-style carbine. The lower is marked "MODEL MOD4SA" and "CAL .223/5.56mm" along with the usual manufacturer's markings. (I don't know where the name M4LE originally came from, but it was on the original cardboard box and listed on CMMG's website for years before they stopped making/listing these). The lower also has the usual A2-style pistol grip and M4-type 6-position stock. The upper receiver is the A4/Flattop variety, with forward assist, ejection port cover, and A2 charging handle, and with phosphated/milspec style full-auto bolt carrier group. The barrel is 16" with A2 flashhider, front sight tower, carbine-length gas tube, and M4 oval handguards, 1-9" twist with CMMG's WASP/Melonited finish. This gun is completely stock as it came from the factory, no modifications of any kind. No problems encountered whatsoever during it's one trip to the range. This would be a great AR for the first time owner or the experienced shooter. Unless you fire 500-1000rds per month, this gun will last for many years to come.
Also included in the asking price (Not pictured):
2x Magpul Gen 2 30rd PMags (used once during a range trip)
5x D&H Aluminum GI-style 30rd magazines, black teflon-coated, with Magpul Foliage Green followers, new in the saran wrap they shipped in. The floorplates are marked "Palmetto State Armory."
Magpul MBUS rear sight (new in wrapper)
200rds Federal American Eagle AE223  .223 Remington 55gr (unopened 20rd boxes)
Blackhawk! Tactical Sportster soft carrying case
Safariland Field Cleaning Kit (Unused) with CLP, brushes, rods, patch holder, patches, silicon gun cloth, and double-ended bristle brush.
 
My asking price is firm. This is not your neighbor's $450 Anderson Mfg AR-15. This a premium AR that retailed for between $800-$900 when they were readily available (before tax). The included extras would also add anywhere between $250-$325 worth of value.
Cash is king, but there are a few trades I would be willing to consider:
Walther P99 QA 9mm (Gen 2 preferred)+ $400 cash
Glock 17, 22 or 31 Gen 3 + $400 cash
Glock 17, 22, or 31 Gen 4 + $350 cash
Glock 34 Gen 3 + $300 cash
Glock 17 Gen 3 RTF2 + $350 cash
Please, don't offer to trade any of the above if they are heavily modified, hacked, dremeled, stippled, chrome-dipped, falling apart, worn out, or otherwise looking like they spent 30 years buried in a gravel pit. I only ever offer to sell/trade well cared for and respected firearms and admire those that do the same.
A further note about these trade offers: after the extra cash is factored in, these are what I would consider to be fair/reasonable offers for the various items listed, assuming they're in good/great condition. For example, I have seen great-looking preowned Gen 3 Glocks offered in stores for around $450. Unless your local gun shop is offering to sell your guns for free, these trade offers are (I feel) a better value than you would get if you tried to sell these on consignment.
 
If you'd like to see more pictures, please ask. If you have any questions, ask. If you like this rifle and want to meet up to buy/trade, please text for fastest response: 817-THREE-SEVEN-ONE-THREE-NINE-TWO-EIGHT
(I am in the north Fort Worth area and can offer to meet you within a reasonable distance)

The manual safety is a thumb activated ambidextrous safety lever (up for SAFE, down for FIRE). The slide locks back after the last shot and a manual slide lock lever is also provided. The light, crisp trigger pull and fiber optic sights make the PMR-30 ideal for target shooting and hunting small game. Slide and barrel are 4140 steel, frame is 7075 aluminum. Grip, slide cover, trigger, mag release, and safety levers are glass reinforced Nylon (Zytel), much like other Kel-Tec  Pistols. Magazine is Also Zytel and holds 30 rounds, with round count ports. Other features include: dual opposing extractors for reliability, heel magazine release to aid in magazine retention, dovetailed aluminum front sight, Picatinny accessory rail under the barrel, Urethane recoil buffer, captive coaxial recoil springs. The barrel is fluted for light weight and effective heat dissipation. PMR30 disassembles for cleaning by removal of a single pin.
